        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={\n  \"contents\": [{\n    \"parts\": [{\n      \"text\": \"You are an expert academic publishing agent. The researcher's manuscript was rejected by their previous target journal. They are now transitioning to their next-highest prioritized journal: '{{ $json['Journal Name'] }}' (Publisher: {{ $json['Publisher'] || 'unspecified' }}).\\n\\nResearch Abstract:\\nColon cancer (CRC) remains a major health burden, highlighting the need for specific, non-invasive biomarkers for early detection. Aberrant DNA methylation is a hallmark of cancer, yet CRC-specific markers are still limited. We performed an integrative multi-omics analysis using genome-wide DNA methylation (Illumina HumanMethylation450K) and RNA-seq data from The Cancer Genome Atlas...\\n\\nPlease generate two comprehensive outputs:\\n\\n1. [COVER LETTER] A tailored, professional cover letter to the Editor-in-Chief of '{{ $json['Journal Name'] }}' referencing the abstract. Keep it under 300 words.\\n\\n2. [AUTHOR GUIDELINES] Detailed manuscript layout rules for '{{ $json['Journal Name'] }}' based on its publisher. Outline the standard manuscript section sequence (e.g., Title Page, Abstract, Intro, Methods, Results, Discussion, References) and specific rules on figure/table formatting and file uploads.\\n\\nFormat your entire response cleanly with clear Markdown headers: '### 📄 COVER LETTER' and '### 📋 SUBMISSION GUIDELINES'.\"\n    }]\n  }]\n}"
      },
